-- Zimbabwe’s Aico Africa Renews Cautionary Statement on Talks
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-01-12T06:46:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/zimbabwe-s-aico-africa-renews-cautionary-statement-on-talks-1-.html
Aico Africa Ltd. (AICO)  of  Zimbabwe , sub-
Saharan  Africa ’s biggest cotton-ginning company, renewed a
cautionary statement.  “Directors are still involved in negotiations for a
potential transaction which, if successful, could have a
material impact on the price of the company’s shares,” the
company said in a announcement published in the Harare-based
Herald newspaper today.  Aico Africa first issued a cautionary statement on the
AfricanSENS website on Jan. 3.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hilton Shone at 
 hshone@bloomberg.net  